  </subsection>
  
<subsection xml:id="sec-cartesian_coordinates-distance">
  <title>Distance</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      Sometimes it is useful to measure the distance between two different points in the plane.
      The distance between points <m>P</m> and <m>Q</m> in the plane is the length of the line segment joining them.
    </p>
    <figure xml:id="fig-distance">
      <caption>The distance between the points <m>P</m> and <m>Q</m>.</caption>
      <image xml:id="img-distance">
	<latex-image >
	  \begin{tikzpicture}
	  \def\xmin{0}
	  \def\xmax{5}
	  \def\ymin{0}
	  \def\ymax{5}
	  \path [draw, help lines, opacity=.5]  (\xmin,\ymin) grid (\xmax,\ymax);
	  \foreach \i in {1,...,5} 
	  \draw [very thick] (\i,2.5pt) -- +(0,-5pt) node [anchor=north, font=\small] {$\i$}
	  (2.5pt,\i) -- +(-5pt,0) node [anchor=east, font=\small] {$\i$};
	  \draw [very thick] (\xmin,0) -- (\xmax,0) node [anchor=south] {$x$};
	  \draw [very thick] (0,\ymin) -- (0,\ymax) node [anchor=west] {$y$};

	  \def\P{(3,2)}
	  \def\Q{(2,3)}

	  \draw [decorate,decoration={brace,mirror,amplitude=5pt}] \P -- \Q;
	  \draw [blue,thick] \P -- \Q;
	  
	  \node at \P {$\bullet$};
	  \node at \P [above right] {$P$};
	  
	  \node at \Q {$\bullet$};
	  \node at \Q [above right] {$Q$};
	  
	  \node at (2.5,2.5) [sloped,above right] {$d$};
	  \end{tikzpicture}
	</latex-image>
      </image>
    </figure>
  </introduction>

  <definition xml:id="defn-distance">
    <p>
      The <term>distance</term>
      <idx>
	<h>Distance</h>
      </idx>
      between the points <m>(x_1,y_1)</m> and <m>(x_2, y_2)</m> in the plane is given by the formula
      <me>
	\sqrt{(x_1 - x_2)^2 + (y_1 - y_2)^2} = \sqrt{(x_2 - x_1)^2 + (y_2 - y_2)^2}
      </me>
    </p>
  </definition>

